result.name: PizzaExpress Times Square

reviews.text: Great location, decent food, decently priced. Service generally quick and good but, funny story, we were given the most dirty glasses to drink from once and on showing this to the manager she just asked (without apology or taking a breath) if we still wanted glasses because, if yes, she'll get us clean ones. We declined and drank from the bottle :) but will not return

I just visited this restaurant in Times Square branch it used to be one of my favorite restaurants but not anymore. I ordered margarita it was thin but not crust and overcooked, cheese was totally dried when I complained about it waitress just said sorry nothing else!! She didnt even ask what was my complaining about. No more!!

One of many locations of the Pizza Express chain.
As with the other branches it offers tasty pizzas and decent wine.
Upstairs on a high floor, making it not as prominent as some of the other.  It is less busy and easier to get a table at mealtimes.

The staffs were rude and inattentive. The waitiress tells me my order was moving without even bothered to check with the kitchen. Every customer had to wave their hands like mad just to get the wait staffs attention. They were roaming the restaurant , but their eyes were either on the floor or straight ahead, while ignoring everything that was going on around them.

A decent restaurant but comes with very bad service which is unlike other PizzaExpress locations. Unorganized, unattentive, and unfriendly service from the restaurant phone which couldn't be reached because the phone connection didnt work and full voicemail, to nobody even come to you to greet nor take your order after seated for 20 mins, to nobody coming to check on your food nor refill your drink after the pizza was served, to when you had to ask multiple times for a simple service for a refill. I have never seen so many hands up from other tables requesting for services.
The only positive is that this location is one of the two which serves gluten free pizza.

reviews.text: It's an eye candy. There's a lot of high end brand, so make sure to bring a lot of money. One of the best place to have a shopping spree

The Time Square of Hong Kong, nice ambience with tons of stores! Movie theater, nice big supermarket nearby and a skip away from a wet mart. Literally has everything. They usually do seasonal events at the front which is pretty interesting.
Very popular shopping centre. Great place to spend time
Shopping center in Wan Chai. Not the fanciest of fanciest, but pretty good brands and not too busy.
The age is showing on the exterior, but the stores stay relevant. Still a great place to get all your shopping done.
